+# Windows Setup Guide
+
+Step-by-step instructions to get the project running on Windows 11.
+
+## Prerequisites (install once)
+
+### 1. Visual Studio Build Tools 2022
+Required to compile the custom PyBullet fork from source.
+
+Download from: https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/visual-cpp-build-tools/
+
+During installation, select the **"Desktop development with C++"** workload only.
+
+### 2. CMake
+```bash
+winget install Kitware.CMake
+```
+Restart your terminal after installation so `cmake` is on PATH.
+
+### 3. Miniconda
+Download and install from: https://docs.conda.io/en/latest/miniconda.html
+
+---
+
+## Step 1 — Create the conda environment
+
+> **Important:** Python 3.13 (the default) is too new for PyBullet. Use 3.10.
+
+```bash
+conda create -n IFT6163_Project python=3.10 -y
+conda activate IFT6163_Project
+```
+
+---
+
+## Step 2 — Install PyTorch
+
+Go to https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/ and select your CUDA version.
+
+**CUDA 12.1 (recommended if you have an NVIDIA GPU):**
+```bash
+pip install torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu121
+```
+
+**CPU only:**
+```bash
+pip install torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu
+```
+
+---
+
+## Step 3 — Fix setuptools / pkg_resources
+
+The conda-installed setuptools is too new and is missing `pkg_resources`. Downgrade it:
+
+```bash
+pip install "setuptools==69.5.1"
+```
+
+Verify it works:
+```bash
+python -c "import pkg_resources; print('ok')"
+```
+
+---
+
+## Step 4 — Build the custom bullet3 fork
+
+The standard `pybullet` on PyPI is missing the `pybullet_envs.minitaur` module.
+You must build the UdeM fork from source.
+
+> **Important:** Run this from a **"Developer Command Prompt for VS 2022"** or from a regular terminal **after** activating the conda environment. The C++ compiler must be on PATH.
+
+```bash
+cd C:\path\to\your\workspace
+git clone https://github.com/montrealrobotics/bullet3.git
+cd bullet3
+pip install -e .
+```
+
+This takes a few minutes (compiling C++).
+
+---
+
+## Step 5 — Fix the bullet3 gym compatibility bug
+
+The minitaur environment has a line that is incompatible with gym >= 0.22. Patch it manually:
+
+Open this file:
+```
+bullet3/examples/pybullet/gym/pybullet_envs/minitaur/envs_v2/locomotion_gym_env.py
+```
+
+Find this method (around line 267):
+```python
+def seed(self, seed=None):
+    self.np_random, self.np_random_seed = gym.utils.seeding.np_random(seed)
+    return [self.np_random_seed]
+```
+
+Change it to:
+```python
+def seed(self, seed=None):
+    self.np_random, self._np_random_seed = gym.utils.seeding.np_random(seed)
+    return [self._np_random_seed]
+```
+
+---
+
+## Step 6 — Install remaining dependencies
+
+```bash
+pip install "gym==0.25.2"
+pip install "protobuf==3.20.3"
+pip install numpy scipy absl-py gin-config attrs six pyserial tensorboard tyro moviepy
+```
+
+---
+
+## Step 7 — Install puppersim
+
+From the root of this repository:
+```bash
+pip install -e .
+```
+
+---
+
+## Step 8 — Verify the installation
+
+```bash
+python puppersim/pupper_example.py
+```
+
+The PyBullet GUI should open and show the Pupper robot doing pushups.
+
+**If the GUI runs slowly**, use the two-process mode:
+```bash
+# Terminal 1
+python puppersim/pupper_minimal_server.py
+
+# Terminal 2
+python puppersim/pupper_example.py --render=False
+```
+
+---
+
+## Step 9 — Test a training run
+
+**Baseline (extrinsic reward only):**
+```bash
+python puppersim/pupper_train_ppo_cont_action.py --env-id PupperGymEnv-v0 --total-timesteps 5000 --seed 1
+```
+
+**With ICM (intrinsic curiosity):**
+```bash
+python puppersim/pupper_train_ppo_cont_action.py --env-id PupperGymEnv-v0 --total-timesteps 5000 --seed 1 --use-icm
+```
+
+---
+
+## Troubleshooting
+
+| Error | Fix |
+|---|---|
+| `No module named 'gym'` | `pip install "gym==0.25.2"` |
+| `Descriptors cannot be created directly` | `pip install "protobuf==3.20.3"` |
+| `No module named 'pkg_resources'` | `pip install "setuptools==69.5.1"` |
+| `can't set attribute 'np_random_seed'` | Apply the patch in Step 5 |
+| `cl.exe not found` during bullet3 build | Open a Developer Command Prompt for VS 2022 |
+| `ModuleNotFoundError: pybullet_envs` | bullet3 build failed — check build output for C++ errors |
+| PyBullet GUI hangs | Use the two-process mode described in Step 8 |
+| `ImportError: pupper_hardware_interface` | Only needed for real robot deployment — safe to ignore for sim |
